                            <comment id="14605646" author="JIRAUSER20210" created="Mon, 21 Aug 2023 23:55:36 -0700"  >Fix Request (21u):&lt;br/&gt;
Hi, This issue also exists in the JDK21U, so i would like to backport this to jdk21u.&lt;br/&gt;
If size of signature-related files in a signed JAR is greater than 8000000 bytes, its failing with Unsupported size for JarEntry . Allowed max size= 8000000bytes. This fix increases the default value to 16000000 byts.&lt;br/&gt;
Its a clean backport and the test pass after change.</comment>
